cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the theoretical framework for understanding the internal representation of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on the compositional structure of activation functions, which is a fundamental aspect of deep learning models, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
